Petsch  .","Germanized form of Sorbian <b>Pěč</b> and <b>Pětš</b>: from the personal name Upper Sorbian <i>Pěč</i>, Lower Sorbian <i>Pětš</i>, (vernacular) equivalents of   Peter  ."]}]},{"name":"Christiana","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Medieval learned feminine form of   Christian .  As a recent revival it represents an elaborated form of   Christina .  It is also sometimes spelled  <b>Christianna</b> , under the influence of the name   Anna ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":7,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":16,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":27,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705206,"age":29,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705207,"age":43,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":45,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Christiana Pitcher was born in 1542, in Hardingham, Norfolk, England. She married Edmund Pitcher about 1560, in Hardingham, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 4 daughters. She died in 1592, at the age of 50, and was buried in Hardingham, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1542–1592":"1542–1592","1525–1583":"1525–1583","1560–1631":"1560–1631","1562–Female":"1562–Surnud","1563–Female":"1563–Surnud","1565–Male":"1565–Surnud","1567–Female":"1567–Surnud","5 January 1560/1":"5. jaanuar 1560","27 Feb 1563":"27. veebruar 1563","21 Mar 1567":"21. märts 1567","1583":"1583","10 September 1592":"10. september 1592","1571":"1571","1560":"1560","1592":"1592","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1525":"1525","1567":"1567","07 Oct 1565":"7. oktoober 1565","1587":"1587","1565":"1565","1631":"1631","1542":"1542","1585":"1585","1563":"1563","1562":"1562","10 May 1562":"10. mai 1562","1549":"1549","about 1560":"umbes 1560","Of Hardingham, Norfolk, England":"Hardingham, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hardingham, Norfolk, England":"Hardingham, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1542–